related_post.text: @monstaslaya Im using this python client: https://browsermobproxypy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/And the code im using is:  dict = {\'port\': 8090} server = Server(path="/var/www/app.seoinsight.io/public_html/app/Libraries/Audit/crawler/browsermobproxy/bin/browsermobproxy.bat options=dict) server.start() proxy = server.create_proxy() from selenium import webdriver profile = webdriver.FirefoxProfile() profile.set_proxy(proxy.selenium_proxy()) driver = webdriver.Firefox(firefox_profile=profile) proxy.new_har("google") driver.get("http://www.google.co.uk") print(driver.page_source) proxy.har # returns a HAR JSON blob pprint.pprint(proxy.har) server.stop() driver.quit()
